
==> this was made for Java in specific { not for Spring Boot in specific }



HTML
-----

==> a small brush-up on HTML,

	<html> : start and end of the file
	
	<head> : starts the head
	
	<body> : context of the file
	
		<h1> <h2> <h3> : all these are various heading levels
		<p> : these create a paragraph
	
	</body>
	</html>
	



--> CDN : content delivery network

==> to add in CNN resources, we must add in this line in the <head> syntax thingy

==> an example link is,
	
	    <link href="http://cdn.jsdelivr.net/webjars/bootstrap/3.3.4/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"/>

		<script src="http://cdn.jsdelivr.net/webjars/jquery/2.1.4/jquery.min.js"></script>

==> the basic change we first notice is the fond change


--> BootStrap Grid System

==> its a robust CSS frame-work

==> its a really standard grid system

==> it divides up the page into rows, and each row has got 12 blocks

==> we will be using,
	<div class = " " >
	
	
	</div>
	
==> and in these, we will have <div class = "row">....</div>

==> and in these, we will have column classes

	like, <div class = "coll-md-1.....12>
			</div>
			





Required Dependdencies
-----------------------

	<dependencies>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
			<artifactId>spring-boot-starter-thymeleaf</artifactId>
		</dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
			<artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
		</dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
			<artifactId>spring-boot-devtools</artifactId>
			<scope>runtime</scope>
			<optional>true</optional>
		</dependency>
		<dependency>
			<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
			<artifactId>spring-boot-starter-test</artifactId>
			<scope>test</scope>
		</dependency>
	</dependencies>
	

